fields.description:
This is associated with QA-706.

The following negative test Cloudformation template creates successfully on a Eucalyptus 4.3.0 cloud:

*Template*
{code}
{
    "AWSTemplateFormatVersion" : "2010-09-09",
    "Description" : "Elastic IP Test - Negative Test - Associate EIP to Instance (Error: You must specify an IP address when mapping to a non-VPC instance)",
    "Parameters" : {
        "ImageId": {
            "Description":"Image Id",
            "Type":"String"
        },
        "InstanceType": {
            "Description":"Instance Type",
            "Type":"String",
            "Default" : "m1.medium",
            "AllowedValues" : [ "m1.small","t1.micro","m1.medium","c1.medium","m1.large", "m1.xlarge", "c1.xlarge", "m2.xlarge", "m3.xlarge", "m2.2xlarge", "m3.2xlarge", "cc1.4xlarge", "m2.4xlarge", "hi1.4xlarge", "cc2.8xlarge", "cg1.4xlarge", "cr1.8xlarge", "hs1.8xlarge" ],
            "ConstraintDescription" : "must be a valid EC2 instance type."
        }
    },
    "Resources" : {
        "EIP": {
            "Type" : "AWS::EC2::EIP",
                "Properties" : {
                    "Domain" : "vpc",
                    "InstanceId": { "Ref": "Instance" }
                }
        },
        "Instance": {
            "Type": "AWS::EC2::Instance",
                "Properties": {
                    "ImageId" : { "Ref":"ImageId" },
                    "InstanceType" : { "Ref":"InstanceType"},
                    "Tags" : [ {"Key" : "Application", "Value" : { "Ref" : "AWS::StackId"} } ]
            }
        }
    },
    "Outputs": {
        "InstanceId" : {
            "Description" : "InstanceId of the newly created EC2 instance",
            "Value" : { "Ref" : "Instance" }
        },
        "AllocationID": {
            "Description" : "Allocation ID of the Elastic IP",
            "Value" : { "Fn::GetAtt" : [ "EIP" , "AllocationId" ] }
        },
        "ElasticIP": {
            "Description" : "Elastic IP",
            "Value" : { "Ref" : "EIP" }
        }
    }
}
{code}

*Output*
{code}
Stack events:
StackEvent AWS::CloudFormation::Stack EIPInstanceTestVPC CREATE_IN_PROGRESS
StackEvent AWS::EC2::Instance Instance CREATE_IN_PROGRESS
StackEvent AWS::EC2::Instance Instance CREATE_IN_PROGRESS
StackEvent AWS::EC2::Instance Instance CREATE_COMPLETE
StackEvent AWS::EC2::EIP EIP CREATE_IN_PROGRESS
StackEvent AWS::EC2::EIP EIP CREATE_IN_PROGRESS
StackEvent AWS::EC2::EIP EIP CREATE_COMPLETE
StackEvent AWS::CloudFormation::Stack EIPInstanceTestVPC CREATE_COMPLETE
{code}

On AWS, the following error is returned:
{code}
"ResourceStatusReason": "You must specify an IP address when mapping to a non-VPC instance"
{code}
AWS Cloudformation events can be viewed below:
{code}
# aws cloudformation describe-stacks  --stack-name EIPInstanceTest
{
    "Stacks": [
        {
            "StackId": "arn:aws:cloudformation:us-east-1:986451091583:stack/EIPInstanceTest/6eebe560-3c81-11e6-9e95-500c219a98d2",
            "Description": "Elastic IP Test - Negative Test - Associate EIP to Instance (Error: You must specify an IP address when mapping to a non-VPC instance)",
            "Parameters": [
                {
                    "ParameterValue": "ami-add615c0",
                    "ParameterKey": "ImageId"
                },
                {
                    "ParameterValue": "m3.medium",
                    "ParameterKey": "InstanceType"
                }
            ],
            "Tags": [],
            "CreationTime": "2016-06-27T16:08:49.088Z",
            "StackName": "EIPInstanceTest",
            "NotificationARNs": [],
            "StackStatus": "ROLLBACK_COMPLETE",
            "DisableRollback": false
        }
    ]
}
{code}
